{"type":"message","id":"2bbe4b19","parentId":"75460b14","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:04:01.203Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fc5f5ad935b04a4f8a2ab3ef","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 2026-07-10\nn: 2\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\nsource_date: 2026-07-01\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\n\nThis is the new normal.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\n→ Book your service\n→ Buy your product\n→ Schedule a meeting\n→ Get support\n\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\n\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\n\nThe question isn't \"should we support AI transactions?\" It's \"how fast can we plug in?\"\n\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\n\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783670641199}}
{"type":"message","id":"b304a183","parentId":"2bbe4b19","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:04:01.209Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7888257beb5f427d9f181a54","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 2026-07-10\nn: 3\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: internal\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴. 𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲'𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\n\nEveryone's chasing the most autonomous, most intelligent, most powerful AI agent.\n\nBut the teams shipping real value? They're doing the opposite.\n\nThey're building BORING agents:\n→ One clear task\n→ Defined success criteria\n→ Human in the loop for edge cases\n→ Fails gracefully, not spectacularly\n\nBoring means predictable. Predictable means trustworthy. Trustworthy means adoption.\n\nThe flashiest AI demo you saw last week? Probably broken in production.\n\nThe boring agent that just works? That's the one getting renewed.\n\nStop optimizing for impressive. Start optimizing for reliable.\n\nWhat's the most boring AI agent you could ship this week?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #SoftwareEngineering #Reliability\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783670641206}}
{"type":"message","id":"d057a2d1","parentId":"b304a183","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:04:23.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **Post 1 is live!** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481256860457787392/\n**Characters:** 888 | **Image:** ✅ fable5-outage\n\n---\n\nNow scheduling posts 2 & 3 for later today:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a89a5d19a6a64c01b19d6859","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"delivery":{"mode":"announce"},"enabled":true,"name":"LinkedIn Post 2 - ChatGPT orders dinner","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"PUBLISH NOW (no confirmation needed):\n\nPost: ChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\n\nBody:\nChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\n\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\n\nThis is the new normal.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\n→ Book your service\n→ Buy your product\n→ Schedule a meeting\n→ Get support\n\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\n\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\n\nThe question isn't \"should we support AI transactions?\" It's \"how fast can we plug in?\"\n\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\n\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\n\n---\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Fetch image from article: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\n2. Or use any relevant existing image from /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/\n3. Publish via li-post.sh with image\n4. Save post record","model":"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas"},"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-10T12:00:00Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"add\", \"job\": {\"delivery\": {\"mode\": \"announce\"}, \"enabled\": true, \"name\": \"LinkedIn Post 2 - ChatGPT orders dinner\", \"payload\": {\"kind\": \"agentTurn\", \"message\": \"PUBLISH NOW (no confirmation needed):\\n\\nPost: ChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\\n\\nBody:\\nChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\\n\\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\\n\\nThis is the new normal.\\n\\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\\n→ Book your service\\n→ Buy your product\\n→ Schedule a meeting\\n→ Get support\\n\\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\\n\\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\\n\\nThe question isn't \\\"should we support AI transactions?\\\" It's \\\"how fast can we plug in?\\\"\\n\\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\\n\\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\\n\\n---\\nINSTRUCTIONS:\\n1. Fetch image from article: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\\n2. Or use any relevant existing image from /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/\\n3. Publish via li-post.sh with image\\n4. Save post record\", \"model\": \"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas\"}, \"schedule\": {\"at\": \"2026-07-10T12:00:00Z\", \"kind\": \"at\"}, \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2da5a802a0bd4efaac19d0c6","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"delivery":{"mode":"announce"},"enabled":true,"name":"LinkedIn Post 3 - Boring AI agents win","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"PUBLISH NOW (no confirmation needed):\n\nPost: The best AI agents are boring. Here's why.\n\nBody:\nThe best AI agents are boring. Here's why.\n\nEveryone's chasing the most autonomous, most intelligent, most powerful AI agent.\n\nBut the teams shipping real value? They're doing the opposite.\n\nThey're building BORING agents:\n→ One clear task\n→ Defined success criteria\n→ Human in the loop for edge cases\n→ Fails gracefully, not spectacularly\n\nBoring means predictable. Predictable means trustworthy. Trustworthy means adoption.\n\nThe flashiest AI demo you saw last week? Probably broken in production.\n\nThe boring agent that just works? That's the one getting renewed.\n\nStop optimizing for impressive. Start optimizing for reliable.\n\nWhat's the most boring AI agent you could ship this week?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #SoftwareEngineering #Reliability\n\n---\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Generate an image for this post using the image-gen skill (LinkedIn mode)\n2. Or use any relevant existing image from /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/\n3. Publish via li-post.sh with image\n4. Save post record","model":"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas"},"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-10T16:00:00Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"add\", \"job\": {\"delivery\": {\"mode\": \"announce\"}, \"enabled\": true, \"name\": \"LinkedIn Post 3 - Boring AI agents win\", \"payload\": {\"kind\": \"agentTurn\", \"message\": \"PUBLISH NOW (no confirmation needed):\\n\\nPost: The best AI agents are boring. Here's why.\\n\\nBody:\\nThe best AI agents are boring. Here's why.\\n\\nEveryone's chasing the most autonomous, most intelligent, most powerful AI agent.\\n\\nBut the teams shipping real value? They're doing the opposite.\\n\\nThey're building BORING agents:\\n→ One clear task\\n→ Defined success criteria\\n→ Human in the loop for edge cases\\n→ Fails gracefully, not spectacularly\\n\\nBoring means predictable. Predictable means trustworthy. Trustworthy means adoption.\\n\\nThe flashiest AI demo you saw last week? Probably broken in production.\\n\\nThe boring agent that just works? That's the one getting renewed.\\n\\nStop optimizing for impressive. Start optimizing for reliable.\\n\\nWhat's the most boring AI agent you could ship this week?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #SoftwareEngineering #Reliability\\n\\n---\\nINSTRUCTIONS:\\n1. Generate an image for this post using the image-gen skill (LinkedIn mode)\\n2. Or use any relevant existing image from /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/\\n3. Publish via li-post.sh with image\\n4. Save post record\", \"model\": \"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas\"}, \"schedule\": {\"at\": \"2026-07-10T16:00:00Z\", \"kind\": \"at\"}, \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\"}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783670641224,"responseId":"cqdQap6uHIyFkuwPt8OP6A4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3af8aa0e","parentId":"d057a2d1","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:04:23.916Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a89a5d19a6a64c01b19d6859","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"6ee4cfee-d947-400d-9c01-7e078510ff17\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"name\": \"LinkedIn Post 2 - ChatGPT orders dinner\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1783670663761,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1783670663761,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"at\": \"2026-07-10T12:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"kind\": \"at\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"PUBLISH NOW (no confirmation needed):\\n\\nPost: ChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\\n\\nBody:\\nChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\\n\\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\\n\\nThis is the new normal.\\n\\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\\n→ Book your service\\n→ Buy your product\\n→ Schedule a meeting\\n→ Get support\\n\\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\\n\\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\\n\\nThe question isn't \\\"should we support AI transactions?\\\" It's \\\"how fast can we plug in?\\\"\\n\\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\\n\\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\\n\\n---\\nINSTRUCTIONS:\\n1. Fetch image from article: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\\n2. Or use any relevant existing image from /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/\\n3. Publish via li-post.sh with image\\n4. Save post record\",\n    \"model\": \"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"to\": \"telegram:264468965\",\n    \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n    \"accountId\": \"default\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1783684800000\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"id":"6ee4cfee-d947-400d-9c01-7e078510ff17","agentId":"main","name":"LinkedIn Post 2 - ChatGPT orders dinner","enabled":true,"deleteAfterRun":true,"createdAtMs":1783670663761,"updatedAtMs":1783670663761,"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-10T12:00:00.000Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"PUBLISH NOW (no confirmation needed):\n\nPost: ChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\n\nBody:\nChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\n\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\n\nThis is the new normal.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\n→ Book your service\n→ Buy your product\n→ Schedule a meeting\n→ Get support\n\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\n\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\n\nThe question isn't \"should we support AI transactions?\" It's \"how fast can we plug in?\"\n\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\n\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\n\n---\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Fetch image from article: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\n2. Or use any relevant existing image from /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/\n3. Publish via li-post.sh with image\n4. Save post record","model":"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","to":"telegram:264468965","channel":"telegram","accountId":"default"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1783684800000}},"isError":false,"timestam