{"type":"message","id":"461d577f","parentId":"e05c1dee","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:14:00.362Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_afc97a06541d4c718fac1a8c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Content Calendar — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n---\n\n## Scheduled Posts — Benchmark-First AI Agent Series\n\n### Post 1: The anatomy of a good benchmark (July 7, 9:00 AM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗳𝘂𝗹 𝗔𝗜 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮 𝘀𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻𝗲?\n\nOne has a benchmark. The other has vibes.\n\nA good benchmark answers three questions:\n\n1. **What's the task?** (specific, not vague)\n2. **What does \"done\" look like?** (verifiable outcome)\n3. **How do you measure it?** (quantifiable metric)\n\nMost teams skip this. They build the agent first, then scramble to figure out if it's working.\n\nFlip it. Write the benchmark BEFORE a single line of code. Make it pass. Then make the agent chase it.\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Every iteration moves the needle. Every failure teaches the system.\n\nThis is TDD for AI. Test first. Agent second.\n\nWhat's one AI project you're building without a clear benchmark?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #TDD #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering\n\n**Characters:** ~950\n\n---\n\n### Post 2: Why most AI agents drift (July 7, 3:00 PM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** ✅ Published — https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480274563235254272/\n\n**Draft:**\n\n[91 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783671240359}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba8a9d77","parentId":"461d577f","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:14:07.157Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_08c5879ab7b042429c22097b","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":150,"offset":1,"path":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-coach/SKILL.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 150, \"offset\": 1, \"path\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-coach/SKILL.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_62e3c804d5a7450eb9dc2256","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -lt /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"ls -lt /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/ 2>/dev/null | head -10\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783671240380,"responseId":"yalQauH0OvbV3PQP74u88AE"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f940a0b","parentId":"ba8a9d77","timestamp":"2026-07-10T08:14:07.230Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_08c5879ab7b042429c22097b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: linkedin-coach\ndescription: Proactive LinkedIn coach. Checks posting cadence, sends daily nudges, proposes next content idea. Run by cron or manually.\nuser-invocable: true\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"requires\":{\"env\":[\"LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID\"]}}}\ntriggers:\n  - \"coach me\"\n  - \"what should i post today\"\n  - \"am i on track\"\n  - \"linkedin check in\"\n  - \"how am i doing on linkedin\"\n  - \"push me to post\"\n  - \"content nudge\"\n---\n\n# LinkedIn Coach Skill\n\n> ⚠️ MANDATORY RULES:\n> 1. **Never publish.** This skill motivates and proposes. Posting uses `linkedin-publish`.\n> 2. **Per-user isolation.** All data keyed by `$TELEGRAM_USER_ID` (from env or cron prompt).\n> 3. **Always be a coach, not a reporter.** Don't just show stats — interpret them. Push the user to act.\n> 4. **DO NOT narrate steps.** Show results directly.\n\n---\n\n## When this skill runs\n\n- **Daily cron** (9 AM user timezone) — called with explicit `TELEGRAM_USER_ID` in prompt\n- **Heartbeat session** — owner gets a quick check each session\n- **User manually asks** — \"what should I post today?\", \"coach me\", etc.\n\n---\n\n## Flow: Daily Coach Check\n\n### Step 1 — Load user context (ONE bash block)\n\n```bash\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nBASE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\"\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\n\n# OAuth check\nACCESS_TOKEN=*** -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].display_name // \"there\"' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\n\n# Strategy: extract cadence line\nCADENCE=\"unknown\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/strategy.md\" ]; then\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \"cadence\\|frequency\\|per week\\|posts/week\" \"$BASE/strategy.md\" | head -1 | sed 's/.*: //')\nfi\n\n# Posts in last 7 days\nPOST_COUNT=$(find \"$BASE/posts/\" -name \"*.md\" -newer \"$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-7d +%Y-%m-%d)\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n\n# Days since last post\nLAST_POST_DATE=$(ls -t \"$BASE/posts/\"*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -oE '[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}')\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\n\n# Next calendar idea\nNEXT_IDEA=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/content-calendar.md\" ]; then\n  NEXT_IDEA=$(grep -A2 \"Status.*Planned\\|Status.*planned\\|\\[ \\]\" \"$BASE/content-calendar.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -5)\nfi\n\necho \"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\"\necho \"CADENCE=$CADENCE\"\necho \"POSTS_LAST_7=$POST_COUNT\"\necho \"LAST_POST=$LAST_POST_DATE\"\necho \"TODAY=$TODAY\"\necho \"NEXT_IDEA_BLOCK=$NEXT_IDEA\"\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Interpret and coach\n\nUse the output to pick one of these tones. Be direct, be human, be Gary Vee — not a status report bot.\n\n**If no token / not connected:**\nSkip this user silently (cron context) or route to onboarding (manual context).\n\n**If POSTS_LAST_7 = 0 and LAST_POST is > 7 days ago (or empty):**\n```\nHey <NAME> 👊\n\nYou haven't posted in over a week. That's the brand dying quietly.\n\nHere's the thing — your audience doesn't remember you if you're not showing up. One post this week is better than the perfect post next month.\n\n<NEXT_IDEA if available — frame as \"Here's your topic for today:\">\n\nReady to write it now?\n```\n\nSend with buttons (put the message text above in the top-level `message`\nfield — Telegram ignores text inside `presentation.blocks`):\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"<the coach message text above>\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"✍️ Write it now\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_write_now\" }, \"style\": \"primary\" },\n        { \"label\": \"💡 Give me another idea\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_new_idea\" } },\n        { \"label\": \"Later\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_later\" }, \"style\": \"secondary\" }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**If POSTS_LAST_7 >= 1 but below cadence target:**\n```\nHey <NAME> — you're posting, which is great. But you're a bit behind your <CADENCE> target this week (<POST_COUNT> posts so far).\n\nOne more push and you're on track. Here's a quick idea:\n\n<NEXT_IDEA>\n\nWant to knock it out now?\n```\n\nSame buttons.\n\n**If on track (meeting or exceeding cadence):**\n```\n<NAME> — you're showing up. <POST_COUNT> posts this week. That's the work.\n\nKeep the momentum. Here's what's up next in your calendar:\n\n<NEXT_IDEA>\n\nWrite it now or save it for later?\n```\n\nButtons (message text goes in the top-level `message` field):\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"<the coach message text above>\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"✍️ Write next post\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_write_now\" }, \"style\": \"primary\" },\n        { \"label\": \"💡 Suggest something else\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_new_idea\" } }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n[33 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783671247227}}
