{"type":"message","id":"e2ccc5a0","parentId":"229fbaeb","timestamp":"2026-07-10T14:13:53.623Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_76f123e9ec1d42549a438333","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-10T12:00:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481316684763553794/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7481316684763553794\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 714\n**Pillar:** AI Agents / Digital Transformation\n**Image:** images/claude-j-space.jpg\n\n## Post Body\n\nChatGPT just ordered dinner. What's your excuse?\n\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\n\nThis is the new normal.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\n→ Book your service\n→ Buy your product\n→ Schedule a meeting\n→ Get support\n\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\n\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\n\nThe question isn't \"should we support AI transactions?\" It's \"how fast can we plug in?\"\n\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\n\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783692833619}}
