{"type":"message","id":"e2f0f6a0","parentId":"15377379","timestamp":"2026-07-11T07:13:52.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question — here's how I balance proactivity vs waiting:\n\n**Automatic (no permission needed):**\n- Morning brief generation (before 10 AM if not sent)\n- Heartbeat checks\n- Background maintenance (memory files, cleanup)\n\n**Proactive but non-intrusive:**\n- Coach nudges (like today's reminder about pending posts)\n- Flagging stale trends research\n- Offering to help when I notice you're behind\n\n**Never without explicit confirmation:**\n- Publishing posts (even drafts require a button tap)\n- Sending messages to external channels\n- Changing configuration or schedules\n\n**The LinkedIn workflow specifically:**\n- Briefs auto-generate at 8 AM-ish\n- Drafts sit in pending until you tap ✅\n- I nudge if you haven't acted by afternoon\n- Publishing ONLY happens on your explicit approval\n\nThe 06:13 nudge was me coaching — you had 3 ready posts and 0 published. That's the Gary Vee energy: direct, push you to ship, but never post without your say-so.\n\nWant me to dial back the nudges, or is the current cadence working?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783754016493,"responseId":"I-1RasfzFt_NwOYPvefa4Ak"}}
